Patch Set 7:

This change makes sense to me.  I'm not sure why we have the unit and functional tests mixed in (only thing I can think of is it makes sure both are run in the gate, but we can take care of that simply by running them both in the gate).  Also, I think the un-compressed environment definitions Sean uses are much easier to read than what we have now.
Patch Set 7: Code-Review+1

Patch Set 7: Workflow+1 Code-Review+2

Makes sense for couple of reasons;
1. we can separately run unit and functional tests which saves time if someone has only updated unit tests and not functional.
2. Identical with what other openstack projects follows
